0px\"><!-- wp:group {\"align\":\"wide\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"default\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group alignwide\"><!-- wp:group {\"layout\":{\"type\":\"flex\",\"flexWrap\":\"nowrap\",\"justifyContent\":\"space-between\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"textColor\":\"Background\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-background-color has-text-color\">© CIAC Copyright 2024. All Rights Reserved.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"style\":{\"elements\":{\"link\":{\"color\":{\"text\":\"var:preset|color|Background\"}}}},\"textColor\":\"Background\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-background-color has-text-color has-link-color\">Designed by Africa News Digest Ltd</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->","footer","","inherit","closed","closed","","36-revision-v1","","","2024-01-16 16:54:03","2024-01-16 16:54:03","","36","https://ciac.rw/?p=59","0","revision","","0");
INSERT INTO `oJegmj1Sz_posts` VALUES("60","1","2024-01-16 17:02:25","2024-01-16 17:02:25","<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In an effort to promote peaceful coexistence and sustainable development, the Centre intervention et d’Action Communautaire (CIAC) has launched a new initiative to prevent conflicts among farmers in the Mugina sector. As a national non-governmental organization (NGO), CIAC aims to improve livelihoods and protect natural resources through environmentally friendly agriculture practices.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Established in June&nbsp;2022, CIAC operates across all provinces of Rwanda, with its head office located in Kigali city. The organization\'s mission is to contribute to the socio-economic development of Rwandan communities by efficiently utilizing natural resources and promoting sustainable agriculture.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the primary objectives of CIAC is to fight against violence within families. To achieve this, the organization leads group discussions to analyze and provide appropriate solutions. By installing a culture of working together in family plans based on the national strategies of the country, CIAC aims to foster harmonious relationships and prevent conflicts from escalating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Moreover, CIAC is dedicated to protecting natural resources and promoting environmentally friendly agricultural techniques. By encouraging farmers to adopt sustainable practices, such as organic farming and efficient water usage, the organization aims to minimize negative impacts on the environment while increasing agricultural productivity.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition, CIAC strives to improve hygiene and sanitation in communities by developing and managing water and sanitation infrastructures. The organization aims to increase access to clean water and sanitation facilities, thereby reducing the risk of waterborne diseases and promoting overall health and well-being.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Promoting gender equality, ICT literacy, and entrepreneurship among women and youth is another key focus area for CIAC. By empowering these marginalized groups, CIAC aims to accelerate sustainable development and create opportunities for economic growth.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Research and education are also important pillars of CIAC\'s work. By studying poverty causes and eradication strategies, the organization seeks to develop informed solutions that address the root causes of poverty. Additionally, CIAC promotes child rights and works towards eliminating child labor through education and advocacy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Lastly, CIAC is committed to providing humanitarian aid to vulnerable populations affected by disasters, wars, or epidemics. By responding swiftly and effectively, the organization aims to alleviate suffering and support affected communities in their recovery efforts.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With its comprehensive approach to community development, CIAC is poised to make a significant impact in the Mugina sector and beyond. By addressing the underlying causes of conflict and promoting sustainable practices, the organization hopes to create a better future for Rwandan farmers and their communities.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->"," CIAC Seeks to Prevent Conflict Among Farmers in the Mugina Sector","","publish","closed","closed","","ciac-seeks-to-prevent-conflict-among-farmers-in-the-mugina-sector","","","2024-01-16 17:18:44","2024-01-16 17:18:44","","0","https://ciac.rw/?p=60","0","post","","0");
INSERT INTO `oJegmj1Sz_posts` VALUES("61","1","2024-01-16 17:02:25","2024-01-16 17:02:25","<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In an effort to promote peaceful coexistence and sustainable development, the Centre intervention et d’Action Communautaire (CIAC) has launched a new initiative to prevent conflicts among farmers in the Mugina sector. As a national non-governmental organization (NGO), CIAC aims to improve livelihoods and protect natural resources through environmentally friendly agriculture practices.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Established in June&nbsp;2022, CIAC operates across all provinces of Rwanda, with its head office located in Kigali city. The organization\'s mission is to contribute to the socio-economic development of Rwandan communities by efficiently utilizing natural resources and promoting sustainable agriculture.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the primary objectives of CIAC is to fight against violence within families. To achieve this, the organization leads group discussions to analyze and provide appropriate solutions. By installing a culture of working together in family plans based on the national strategies of the country, CIAC aims to foster harmonious relationships and prevent conflicts from escalating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Moreover, CIAC is dedicated to protecting natural resources and promoting environmentally friendly agricultural techniques. By encouraging farmers to adopt sustainable practices, such as organic farming and efficient water usage, the organization aims to minimize negative impacts on the environment while increasing agricultural productivity.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition, CIAC strives to improve hygiene and sanitation in communities by developing and managing water and sanitation infrastructures. The organization aims to increase access to clean water and sanitation facilities, thereby reducing the risk of waterborne diseases and promoting overall health and well-being.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Promoting gender equality, ICT literacy, and entrepreneurship among women and youth is another key focus area for CIAC. By empowering these marginalized groups, CIAC aims to accelerate sustainable development and create opportunities for economic growth.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Research and education are also important pillars of CIAC\'s work. By studying poverty causes and eradication strategies, the organization seeks to develop informed solutions that address the root causes of poverty. Additionally, CIAC promotes child rights and works towards eliminating child labor through education and advocacy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Lastly, CIAC is committed to providing humanitarian aid to vulnerable populations affected by disasters, wars, or epidemics. By responding swiftly and effectively, the organization aims to alleviate suffering and support affected communities in their recovery efforts.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With its comprehensive approach to community development, CIAC is poised to make a significant impact in the Mugina sector and beyond. By addressing the underlying causes of conflict and promoting sustainable practices, the organization hopes to create a better future for Rwandan farmers and their communities.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->"," CIAC Seeks to Prevent Conflict Among Farmers in the Mugina Sector","","inherit","closed","closed","","60-revision-v1","","","2024-01-16 17:02:25","2024-01-16 17:02:25","","60","https://ciac.rw/?p=61","0","revision","","0");
INSERT INTO `oJegmj1Sz_posts` VALUES("63","1","2024-01-16 17:09:01","2024-01-16 17:09:01","<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Kigali, Rwanda -</strong> In a bid to improve livelihoods and promote sustainable development, the Centre intervention et d’Action Communautaire (CIAC) has partnered with AGROPLAST, a leading manufacturer of eco-friendly agricultural and Environmental solutions. The collaboration aims to distribute energy-saving cook stoves to communities across Rwanda.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>CIAC, a national non-governmental organization, has been at the forefront of initiatives that contribute to the socio-economic development of Rwandan communities. With a focus on efficient use of natural resources and environmentally friendly agriculture, CIAC has been working tirelessly to improve living conditions and promote sustainable practices.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The newly formed partnership with AGROPLAST is set to make a significant impact on the lives of the local population. Energy-saving cook stoves have been identified as a key solution for reducing deforestation and improving air quality in households. These stoves are designed to use less firewood while providing efficient cooking methods, ultimately saving energy and reducing harmful emissions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The collaboration will see CIAC and AGROPLAST working together to distribute these cook stoves in all provinces of Rwanda. By providing access to clean and efficient cooking technology, the organizations hope to address issues such as indoor air pollution and the depletion of natural resources.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"We are thrilled to partner with AGROPLAST in this important initiative,\" said Drocella, the President of CIAC. \"Energy-saving cook stoves are not only environmentally friendly but also have a positive impact on the health and well-being of families. This partnership will enable us to reach more communities and make a real difference in their lives.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":64,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://ciac.rw/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/WhatsApp-Image-2024-01-16-at-12.12.19-PM-1-1-1024x768.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-64\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>AGROPLAST, known for its innovative solutions in the agricultural and Environment sector, is equally excited about the collaboration. \"We believe that sustainable development starts at the grassroots level,\" said Nduwayezu Leon, CEO of AGROPLAST. \"By providing energy-saving cook stoves, we are not only conserving natural resources but also empowering communities to lead healthier and more sustainable lives.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The distribution of the cook stoves will be accompanied by training sessions on their proper use and maintenance. CIAC and AGROPLAST will work closely with local communities to ensure that the benefits of this initiative are maximized.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As CIAC continues to fulfill its mission of improving livelihoods and promoting environmentally friendly practices, this partnership with AGROPLAST marks a significant step towards achieving sustainable development in Rwanda. By addressing the pressing issues of deforestation and indoor air pollution, the organizations hope to create a brighter and healthier future for all Rwandans.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->","CIAC Partners with AGROPLAST to Distribute Energy Saving Cook Stove","","publish","open","open","","ciac-partners-with-agroplast-to-distribute-energy-saving-cook-stove","","","2024-01-16 17:09:01","2024-01-16 17:09:01","","0","https://ciac.rw/?p=63","0","post","","0");
INSERT INTO `oJegmj1Sz_posts` VALUES("64","1","2024-01-16 17:08:57","2024-01-16 17:08:57","","WhatsApp-Image-2024-01-16-at-12.12.19-PM-1-1","","inherit","open","closed","","whatsapp-image-2024-01-16-at-12-12-19-pm-1-1","","","2024-01-16 17:08:57","2024-01-16 17:08:57","","63","https://ciac.rw/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/WhatsApp-Image-2024-01-16-at-12.12.19-PM-1-1.jpeg","0","attachment","image/jpeg","0");
INSERT INTO `oJegmj1Sz_posts` VALUES("65","1","2024-01-16 17:09:01","2024-01-16 17:09:01","<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Kigali, Rwanda -</strong> In a bid to improve livelihoods and promote sustainable development, the Centre intervention et d’Action Communautaire (CIAC) has partnered with AGROPLAST, a leading manufacturer of eco-friendly agricultural and Environmental solutions. The collaboration aims to distribute energy-saving cook stoves to communities across Rwanda.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>CIAC, a national non-governmental organization, has been at the forefront of initiatives that contribute to the socio-economic development of Rwandan communities. With a focus on efficient use of natural resources and environmentally friendly agriculture, CIAC has been working tirelessly to improve living conditions and promote sustainable practices.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The newly formed partnership with AGROPLAST is set to make a significant impact on the lives of the local population. Energy-saving cook stoves have been identified as a key solution for reducing deforestation and improving air quality in households. These stoves are designed to use less firewood while providing efficient cooking methods, ultimately saving energy and reducing harmful emissions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The collaboration will see CIAC and AGROPLAST working together to distribute these cook stoves in all provinces of Rwanda. By providing access to clean and efficient cooking technology, the organizations hope to address issues such as indoor air pollution and the depletion of natural resources.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"We are thrilled to partner with AGROPLAST in this important initiative,\" said Drocella, the President of CIAC. \"Energy-saving cook stoves are not only environmentally friendly but also have a positive impact on the health and well-being of families. This partnership will enable us to reach more communities and make a real difference in their lives.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":64,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://ciac.rw/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/WhatsApp-Image-2024-01-16-at-12.12.19-PM-1-1-1024x768.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-64\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>AGROPLAST, known for its innovative solutions in the agricultural and Environment sector, is equally excited about the collaboration. \"We believe that sustainable development starts at the grassroots level,\" said Nduwayezu Leon, CEO of AGROPLAST. \"By providing energy-saving cook stoves, we are not only conserving natural resources but also empowering communities to lead healthier and more sustainable lives.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The distribution of the cook stoves will be accompanied by training sessions on their proper use and maintenance. CIAC and AGROPLAST will work closely with local communities to ensure that the benefits of this initiative are maximized.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As CIAC continues to fulfill its mission of improving livelihoods and promoting environmentally friendly practices, this partnership with AGROPLAST marks a significant step towards achieving sustainable development in Rwanda. By addressing the pressing issues of deforestation and indoor air pollution, the organizations hope to create a brighter and healthier future for all Rwandans.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->","CIAC Partners with AGROPLAST to Distribute Energy Saving Cook Stove","","inherit","closed","closed","","63-revision-v1","","","2024-01-16 17:09:01","2024-01-16 17:09:01","","63","https://ciac.rw/?p=65","0","revision","","0");
INSERT INTO `oJegmj1Sz_posts` VALUES("66","1","2024-01-16 17:14:47","2024-01-16 17:14:47","<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Rwanda- In a bid to contribute to the country\'s sustainable development and combat climate change, the Centre intervention et d\'Action Communautaire (CIAC) participated in the 2023-2024 Tree Planting Campaign. The national non-governmental organization (NGO) mobilized its resources and volunteers to plant trees across all its intervention areas.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Established in June&nbsp;2022, CIAC has been dedicated to improving the livelihoods of Rwandan communities by promoting environmentally friendly agriculture and efficient use of natural resources. With a mission to foster socio-economic development, the NGO has been actively involved in various initiatives aimed at protecting the environment and uplifting local communities.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The tree planting campaign, organized by the Rwandan government, aimed to increase the country\'s forest cover and mitigate the effects of climate change. Recognizing the importance of this endeavor, CIAC joined hands with other organizations and individuals to plant trees in different regions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"We are proud to be part of this important initiative,\" said Drocella, the President of CIAC. \"Planting trees not only helps combat climate change but also provides numerous benefits such as improving air quality, preserving biodiversity, and preventing soil erosion.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>CIAC\'s volunteers, including staff members and community members, enthusiastically participated in the tree planting activities. The organization prioritized areas that were most vulnerable to deforestation and degradation, ensuring that the newly planted trees would have a lasting impact on the environment.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":23,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"https://ciac.rw/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/IMG_1500.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-23\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition to its commitment to environmental conservation, CIAC also focuses on various other social issues. The organization actively fights against violence in families by facilitating group discussions and providing solutions. It also promotes gender equality, entrepreneurship, and I.C.T education among women and youth as a means of accelerating sustainable development.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Furthermore, CIAC is dedicated to promoting hygiene and sanitation through the development of water and sanitation infrastructures. By increasing access to clean water and sanitation facilities, the NGO aims to improve the overall health and well-being of communities.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As part of its humanitarian efforts, CIAC also works towards protecting child rights, eradicating child labor, and providing assistance during times of vulnerability such as disasters, wars, or epidemics.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By participating in the&nbsp;2023-2024 Tree Planting Campaign, CIAC has once again demonstrated its commitment to the sustainable development of Rwanda. Through their collective efforts, CIAC and other organizations are striving to create a greener and more prosperous future for all Rwandans.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->","CIAC Joins Forces in Massive Tree Planting Initiative","","publish","open","open","","ciac-joins-forces-in-massive-tree-planting-initiative","","","2024-04-02 16:18:13","2024-04-02 16:18:13","","0","https://ciac.rw/?p=66","0","post","","0");
INSERT INTO `oJegmj1Sz_posts` VALUES("67","1","2024-01-16 17:14:47","2024-01-16 17:14:47","<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Rwanda- In a bid to contribute to the country\'s sustainable development and combat climate change, the Centre intervention et d\'Action Communautaire (CIAC) participated in the 2023-2024 Tree Planting Campaign. The national non-governmental organization (NGO) mobilized its resources and volunteers to plant trees across all its intervention areas.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Established in June&nbsp;2022, CIAC has been dedicated to improving the livelihoods of Rwandan communities by promoting environmentally friendly agriculture and efficient use of natural resources. With a mission to foster socio-economic development, the NGO has been actively involved in various initiatives aimed at protecting the environment and uplifting local communities.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The tree planting campaign, organized by the Rwandan government, aimed to increase the country\'s forest cover and mitigate the effects of climate change. Recognizing the importance of this endeavor, CIAC joined hands with other organizations and individuals to plant trees in different regions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"We are proud to be part of this important initiative,\" said Drocella, the President of CIAC. \"Planting trees not only helps combat climate change but also provides numerous benefits such as improving air quality, preserving biodiversity, and preventing soil erosion.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>CIAC\'s volunteers, including staff members and community members, enthusiastically participated in the tree planting activities. The organization prioritized areas that were most vulnerable to deforestation and degradation, ensuring that the newly planted trees would have a lasting impact on the environment.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":23,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"https://ciac.rw/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/IMG_1500.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-23\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition to its commitment to environmental conservation, CIAC also focuses on various other social issues. The organization actively fights against violence in families by facilitating group discussions and providing solutions. It also promotes gender equality, entrepreneurship, and I.C.T education among women and youth as a means of accelerating sustainable development.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Furthermore, CIAC is dedicated to promoting hygiene and sanitation through the development of water and sanitation infrastructures. By increasing access to clean water and sanitation facilities, the NGO aims to improve the overall health and well-being of communities.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As part of its humanitarian efforts, CIAC also works towards protecting child rights, eradicating child labor, and providing assistance during times of vulnerability such as disasters, wars, or epidemics.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By participating in the&nbsp;2023-2024 Tree Planting Campaign, CIAC has once again demonstrated its commitment to the sustainable development of Rwanda. Through their collective efforts, CIAC and other organizations are striving to create a greener and more prosperous future for all Rwandans.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->","CIAC Joins Forces in Massive Tree Planting Initiative","","inherit","closed","closed","","66-revision-v1","","","2024-01-16 17:14:47","2024-01-16 17:14:47","","66","https://ciac.rw/?p=67","0","revision","","0");
INSERT INTO `oJegmj1Sz_posts` VALUES("68","1","2024-01-16 17:16:13","2024-01-16 17:16:13","<!-- wp:template-part {\"slug\":\"header\",\"theme\":\"greengrass\",\"tagName\":\"header\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"margin\":{\"top\":\"0px\"}}}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\" style=\"margin-top:0px\"><!-- wp:cover {\"url\":\"https://ciac.rw/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/53299587626_c3909a21ca_k.jpg\",\"id\":9,\"hasParallax\":true,\"isRepeated\":true,\"dimRatio\":40,\"minHeight\":800,\"align\":\"full\",\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"padding\":{\"top\":\"20px\",\"right\":\"20px\",\"bottom\":\"20px\",\"left\":\"20px\"}}}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-cover alignfull has-parallax is-repeated\" style=\"padding-top:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-bottom:20px;padding-left:20px;min-height:800px\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-background-dim-40 has-background-dim\"></span><div role=\"img\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-9 has-parallax is-repeated\" style=\"background-position:50{3338937df10194424d40636f8c2716dc2160f64fc18487a5744941c2d65e9ddb} 50{3338937df10194424d40636f8c2716dc2160f64fc18487a5744941c2d65e9ddb};background-image:url(https://ciac.rw/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/53299587626_c3909a21ca_k.jpg)\"></div><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container\"><!-- wp:group {\"align\":\"wide\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group alignwide\"><!-- wp:group {\"align\":\"wide\",\"className\":\"nivo-caption\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"default\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group alignwide nivo-caption\"><!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\"><!-- wp:column {\"style\":{\"color\":{\"background\":\"#019443d6\"},\"spacing\":{\"padding\":{\"top\":\"3em\",\"right\":\"3em\",\"bottom\":\"3em\",\"left\":\"3em\"}}}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column has-background\" style=\"background-color:#019443d6;padding-top:3em;padding-right:3em;padding-bottom:3em;padding-left:3em\"><!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"margin\":{\"top\":\"0px\"}},\"typography\":{\"fontStyle\":\"normal\",\"fontWeight\":\"700\"}},\"fontSize\":\"big\",\"fontFamily\":\"satisfy\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-satisfy-font-family has-big-font-size\" style=\"margin-top:0px;font-style:normal;font-weight:700\">Building a Sustainable Future: Efficient Resources, Environmentally Friendly Agriculture</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"lineHeight\":\"1.6\"}},\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\" style=\"line-height:1.6\">CIAC (Centre intervention et d’Action Communautaire) is a National NGO: a non-profit making, non-governmental organization with its head office in Kigali city (Kicukiro District. It operates in all provinces of Rwanda. CIAC was established in June 2022.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button {\"backgroundColor\":\"white\",\"textColor\":\"secondary\",\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"letterSpacing\":\"2px\"}}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\" style=\"letter-spacing:2px\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-secondary-color has-white-background-color has-text-color has-background wp-element-button\" href=\"https://ciac.rw/?page_id=50\">Learn More</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:cover --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"tagName\":\"main\",\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"margin\":{\"top\":\"0px\",\"bottom\":\"0px\"}}},\"layout\":{\"type\":\"default\"}} -->\n<main class=\"wp-block-group\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px\"><!-- wp:group {\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"margin\":{\"top\":\"0px\",\"bottom\":\"0px\"},\"padding\":{\"top\":\"60px\",\"right\":\"20px\",\"bottom\":\"60px\",\"left\":\"20px\"}}},\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;padding-top:60px;padding-right:20px;padding-bottom:60px;padding-left:20px\"><!-- wp:group {\"align\":\"wide\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"default\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group alignwide\"><!-- wp:group {\"align\":\"wide\",\"className\":\"section_head\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"default\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group alignwide section_head\"><!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"level\":4,\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontStyle\":\"normal\",\"fontWeight\":\"500\"}},\"className\":\"section_sub_title\",\"fontSize\":\"body-text\",\"fontFamily\":\"catamaran\"} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center section_sub_title has-catamaran-font-family has-body-text-font-size\" style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:500\"><strong>CIAC’s intervention domains</strong>:</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"margin\":{\"top\":\"0px\"}},\"typography\":{\"fontStyle\":\"normal\",\"fontWeight\":\"700\",\"fontSize\":\"40px\"},\"elements\":{\"link\":{\"color\":{\"text\":\"var:preset|color|primary\"}}}},\"textColor\":\"primary\",\"className\":\"section_title\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center section_title has-primary-color has-text-color has-link-color\" style=\"margin-top:0px;font-size:40px;font-style:normal;font-weight:700\">Promoting Environmental Friendly Practices</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">CIAC has been established in January 2022 with the overall goal of contributing to the promotion of Rwandan communities by improving livelihood through efficient use of natural resources and promoting environmentally friendly agriculture for sustainable development.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":\"10px\"} -->\n<div style=\"height:10px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:group {\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"padding\":{\"top\":\"20px\",\"right\":\"20px\",\"bottom\":\"20px\",\"left\":\"20px\"}},\"border\":{\"radius\":\"12px\"}},\"backgroundColor\":\"white\",\"className\":\"service-box\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-box has-white-background-color has-background\" style=\"border-radius:12px;padding-top:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-bottom:20px;padding-left:20px\"><!-- wp:group {\"className\":\"service-box-thumb\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"default\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-box-thumb\"><!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":21,\"width\":\"240px\",\"height\":\"160px\",\"scale\":\"cover\",\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"https://ciac.rw/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/52954768134_5fb955386c_3k.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-21\" style=\"object-fit:cover;width:240px;height:160px\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"margin\":{\"bottom\":\"0px\",\"top\":\"0px\"}}},\"className\":\"service-box-content\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-box-content\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px\"><!-- wp:group {\"className\":\"service-box-icon\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-box-icon\"><!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":635,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img src=\"https://ciac.rw/wp-content/themes/greengrass/images/ser-icon1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-635\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"level\":3,\"style\":{\"elements\":{\"link\":{\"color\":{\"text\":\"var:preset|color|primary\"}}}},\"textColor\":\"primary\"} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center has-primary-color has-text-color has-link-color\">Environment management.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">This activity includes activities such as assessing and mitigating environmental risks, implementing waste management strategies, conserving natural resources, promoting renewable energy sources, and adhering to environmental regulations.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"margin\":{\"top\":\"0px\",\"bottom\":\"0px\"}}},\"className\":\"service-number\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-number\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:group {\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"padding\":{\"top\":\"20px\",\"right\":\"20px\",\"bottom\":\"20px\",\"left\":\"20px\"}},\"border\":{\"radius\":\"12px\"}},\"backgroundColor\":\"white\",\"className\":\"service-box\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-box has-white-background-color has-background\" style=\"border-radius:12px;padding-top:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-bottom:20px;padding-left:20px\"><!-- wp:group {\"className\":\"service-box-thumb\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"default\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-box-thumb\"><!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":22,\"width\":\"240px\",\"height\":\"160px\",\"scale\":\"cover\",\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"https://ciac.rw/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/53390679189_63fb7c45cd_5k.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-22\" style=\"object-fit:cover;width:240px;height:160px\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"margin\":{\"top\":\"0px\",\"bottom\":\"0px\"}}},\"className\":\"service-box-content\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-box-content\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px\"><!-- wp:group {\"className\":\"service-box-icon\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-box-icon\"><!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":662,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img src=\"https://ciac.rw/wp-content/themes/greengrass/images/ser-icon2.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-662\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"level\":3,\"style\":{\"elements\":{\"link\":{\"color\":{\"text\":\"var:preset|color|primary\"}}}},\"textColor\":\"primary\"} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center has-primary-color has-text-color has-link-color\">Climate change adaptation and mitigation</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">We work towards developing strategies and implementing measures that help societies and ecosystems adapt to the changing climate conditions while also working towards reducing the causes of climate change.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"margin\":{\"top\":\"0px\",\"bottom\":\"0px\"}}},\"className\":\"service-number\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-number\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:group {\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"padding\":{\"top\":\"20px\",\"right\":\"20px\",\"bottom\":\"20px\",\"left\":\"20px\"}},\"border\":{\"radius\":\"12px\"}},\"backgroundColor\":\"white\",\"className\":\"service-box\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-box has-white-background-color has-background\" style=\"border-radius:12px;padding-top:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-bottom:20px;padding-left:20px\"><!-- wp:group {\"className\":\"service-box-thumb\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"default\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-box-thumb\"><!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":23,\"width\":\"240px\",\"height\":\"160px\",\"scale\":\"cover\",\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"https://ciac.rw/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/IMG_1500.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-23\" style=\"object-fit:cover;width:240px;height:160px\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"margin\":{\"top\":\"0px\",\"bottom\":\"0px\"}}},\"className\":\"service-box-content\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-box-content\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px\"><!-- wp:group {\"className\":\"service-box-icon\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-box-icon\"><!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":28,\"width\":\"60px\",\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"https://ciac.rw/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/conflict-management-icon-design-vector.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-28\" style=\"width:60px\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"level\":3,\"style\":{\"elements\":{\"link\":{\"color\":{\"text\":\"var:preset|color|primary\"}}}},\"textColor\":\"primary\"} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center has-primary-color has-text-color has-link-color\">Conflict management</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">By promoting open dialogue, understanding different perspectives, and finding common ground, conflict management aims to foster harmony, improve relationships, and enhance productivity in both personal and professional settings.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"margin\":{\"top\":\"0px\",\"bottom\":\"0px\"}}},\"className\":\"service-number\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-number\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:group {\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"padding\":{\"top\":\"20px\",\"right\":\"20px\",\"bottom\":\"20px\",\"left\":\"20px\"}},\"border\":{\"radius\":\"12px\"}},\"backgroundColor\":\"white\",\"className\":\"service-box\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-box has-white-background-color has-background\" style=\"border-radius:12px;padding-top:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-bottom:20px;padding-left:20px\"><!-- wp:group {\"className\":\"service-box-thumb\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"default\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-box-thumb\"><!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":24,\"width\":\"240px\",\"height\":\"160px\",\"scale\":\"cover\",\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"https://ciac.rw/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/IMG_1498.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-24\" style=\"object-fit:cover;width:240px;height:160px\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"margin\":{\"top\":\"0px\",\"bottom\":\"0px\"}}},\"className\":\"service-box-content\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-box-content\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px\"><!-- wp:group {\"className\":\"service-box-icon\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-box-icon\"><!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":665,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img src=\"https://ciac.rw/wp-content/themes/greengrass/images/ser-icon4.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-665\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\",\"level\":3,\"style\":{\"elements\":{\"link\":{\"color\":{\"text\":\"var:preset|color|primary\"}}}},\"textColor\":\"primary\"} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center has-primary-color has-text-color has-link-color\">Good governance and Economic development.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">At our organization, we focus on promoting good governance and economic development. We believe that effective governance systems and policies are crucial for creating a conducive environment for sustainable economic growth and prosperity.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"style\":{\"spacing\":{\"margin\":{\"top\":\"0px\",\"bottom\":\"0px\"}}},\"className\":\"service-number\",\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group service-number\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"style\